m_q.target_metric: Number of identity theft reports in 2007 concerning people ages 40 or older (rounded to nearest thousand)
sub_questions: What is the total number of reports in 2007?
What percentage of 2024 reports are identity theft?
What percentage of 2024 identity theft reports are from ages 40+?
How to apply 2024 distribution patterns to 2007 data?

schema_conflicts: Year column in 2024_CSN_Report_Count.csv is float64 but represents integer years
Percentage column in 2024_CSN_Report_Categories.csv is object/string with % symbol
Last row in 2024_CSN_Identity_Theft_Reports_by_Age.csv contains metadata text instead of data

scale_issues: 2024_CSN_Report_Count.csv shows increasing report counts over time (2001-2020)
Need to normalize 2007 data using 2024 proportions
Age distribution data only available for 2024

format_notes: 2024_CSN_Identity_Theft_Reports_by_Age.csv has metadata row at end with text explanation
Year values in 2024_CSN_Report_Count.csv have .0 decimal notation

constraints: Total 2024 reports = 6,470,000 (sum of # of Reports in 2024_CSN_Report_Categories.csv)
Age data only available for 2024, must be applied proportionally to 2007
derived_filters: Calculate proportion of 40+ reports from 2024 age distribution
Apply same proportion to estimated 2007 identity theft reports
statistical_tests: Check if age distribution is consistent across years (assumption)
Verify that 2024 proportions can be applied to 2007
Validate that rounding to nearest thousand is appropriate
output_format_requirements: Round final result to nearest thousand
